# Minimal UI Copy

This portfolio favors a clean, uncluttered layout. Do not add descriptive or explanatory text unless the user explicitly asks for it.

## Do not add by default

- Section subtitles under headings (e.g. "Technologies I work with", "Have a project in mind...")
- Helper text under labels or cards (e.g. "Hover the card — stacked layers fan out...")
- Secondary lines on cards (e.g. role tags, "Connect professionally", "View my code")
- Feature blurbs, tooltips, or "Read more" / "Learn more" copy on visual components
- Redundant descriptions in demos, galleries, timelines, or carousels when the title/icon already communicates intent

## Prefer instead

- Titles and labels only — short, scannable headings
- Icons, imagery, and interaction over prose
- One primary heading per section; skip the paragraph beneath it unless requested

## When adding UI

- If a component template includes `description`, `subtitle`, or helper props — omit them or leave them empty unless the user asks for copy
- When refactoring sections, remove existing subtitles/helper text if they crowd the layout
- Ask before adding marketing-style or explanatory paragraphs to pages, cards, or feature blocks

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — crowded
<SectionHeader
  title="Experience & Skills"
  subtitle="Technologies I work with — click a node to explore"
/>

// ✅ GOOD
<h2 className="text-3xl font-bold">Experience & Skills</h2>
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<p className="text-muted-foreground">
  Hover the card — stacked layers fan out. Tap a layer to open LinkedIn, GitHub, or email.
</p>

// ✅ GOOD — no helper paragraph; the card speaks for itself
<SocialCard title="Socials" socialLinks={socialLinks} />
```
